    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>No. 153.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 191.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch No. 54, in relation
                        to the case of Walter Jackson, who was charged with the crime of piracy and
                        assault with intent to commit murder on board a British vessel on the high
                        seas, I inclose for your information a copy of an instruction<note n="*" xml:id="d155fn1">See instruction No. 424 to consul-general at
                            Shanghai.</note> of this date, addressed by the Department to Mr. George
                        F. Seward, the consul-general of the United States at Shanghai, in reference
                        to this case.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
